	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It looks easy and it's something I've wanted to do, also.  You should be able to wire the new switches right to the chip on the controller PCB.  I'm not sure what you mean about the "teeth" part.
<br />
<br />Most of the joysticks are digital, if it has 4 switches it should work (as long as it doesn't restrict where the stick can actually move).
<br />
<br />I don't know where the best parts are, but I'd recommend looking around on forums where people are building control panels for MAME.  There are different styles of buttons and joysticks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


