<br />
<br />by teeth I mean the "E" shaped pieces interlocking where the buttons actually make contact with the board.  
<br />
<br />back to Tepples, Good to hear that works, I couldn't think of why it wouldn't, but I wasn't sure after seeing the Giant NES controller method.  To me, it seems easiest just to go to each button since there's really no need to conserve wire or space since its just one small chip in a big empty wooden box.  Don't arcade buttons have some industrial name as well?

		

